    "As the above shows, ancestral graphs primarily provide information about the ancestral and parental relationships in the underlying DAG, hence their name.",
    "Figure 11b shows the ancestral graph which represents the relationships between the observed variables in Fig. 11a.",
    "Richardson and Spirtes (2002) state two key conditions in the definition of an ancestral graph:",
    "• there are no partially directed cycles.",
    "A partially directed cycle consists of an anterior path from A to B together with an edge B → A or B ↔ A."
